@@ -0,0 +1,20 @@
+# Runtime Bundle Packaging
+
+Hive's release artifact is a relocatable runtime bundle, not a single-file Ruby
+binary.
+
+The TUI depends on `bubbletea` and `lipgloss`, whose Ruby gems ship
+platform-specific native payloads. Wrapping those gems into a monolithic binary
+would make the release path depend on fragile native extraction behavior.
+
+The release workflow therefore builds one bundle per target:
+
+- `ruby/` portable Ruby prefix
+- `vendor/bundle/` gems installed for the target platform
+- `app/` Hive source, templates, schemas, and lockfile
+- `bin/hive` launcher that pins Bundler to the bundled app
+
+Homebrew, AUR, and `install.sh` all install the same tarball and write an
+`INSTALL-CHANNEL` marker so `hive update` delegates back to the owning channel.
+Fresh installs use XDG paths for global config, data, state, and cache; existing
+`~/Dev/hive` installs and explicit `$HIVE_HOME` continue to work.
