+# Install Hive With A Coding Agent
+
+Paste this prompt into Claude Code, Codex, Pi, or another coding agent that can
+run shell commands. Stop and ask before changing anything not described here.
+
+```text
+Install Hive from GitHub Releases, then verify it.
+
+Rules:
+- Do not install Ruby or gems for Hive; official release bundles include their own Ruby runtime.
+- Do not overwrite an existing unrelated `hive` command. If one exists, use the installer fallback command name `hv`.
+- Do not write directly into agent skill directories such as ~/.claude/skills or ~/.codex/skills. Skills are installed only through the host agent marketplace when available.
+- If any command fails, stop and report the command, exit code, and stderr summary.
+
+Steps:
+1. Detect the host:
+   - macOS: use Homebrew if `brew` exists.
+   - Arch Linux: use `yay -S hive-bin` if `yay` exists.
+   - Otherwise use the release installer:
+     `curl -fsSL https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/latest/download/install.sh | bash`
+2. For macOS with Homebrew, run:
+   `brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive`
+3. For Arch with yay, run:
+   `yay -S hive-bin`
+4. If neither package-manager path applies, run the curl installer above.
+5. Determine the command name:
+   - Prefer `hive` when `command -v hive` resolves to the installed Hive command.
+   - Use `hv` if the installer reported that `hive` was already occupied.
+6. Verify:
+   - `<cmd> --version`
+   - `<cmd> doctor`
+7. Ask whether to run `<cmd> init .` in the current working directory. Run it only after confirmation.
+8. If this agent has a real marketplace/plugin system:
+   - Add the Hive skills marketplace or package repository when provided by the user or organization.
+   - Install the Hive skills package through that marketplace.
+   - Run `<cmd> doctor` again.
+9. If this agent has no marketplace/plugin install command, report that the core Hive binary is installed and skills must be installed manually through the agent's native marketplace when available.
+
+Report the installed command path, Hive version, doctor result, and whether init was run.
+```
