@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@
+---
+name: hive
+description: Drive the Hive folder-as-agent pipeline from an installed hive CLI.
+---
+
+# Hive Skill
+
+Use when the user asks to operate Hive tasks, inspect Hive status, move a task
+through a stage, or diagnose a Hive pipeline state.
+
+Before acting:
+
+1. Run `hive --version` or `hv --version` to identify the installed command.
+2. Prefer JSON-capable commands for automation: `status --json`, workflow verbs
+   with `--json`, `doctor --json`, and daemon commands with `--json`.
+3. Treat files under `.hive-state/` as user-owned project state. Do not edit
+   plan/task/review files unless the user asked you to answer, triage, or fix
+   that task.
+
+Useful commands:
+
+- `hive status --json`
+- `hive new PROJECT "idea"`
+- `hive brainstorm SLUG --from 1-inbox`
+- `hive plan SLUG --from 2-brainstorm`
+- `hive develop SLUG --from 3-plan`
+- `hive open-pr SLUG --from 4-execute`
+- `hive review SLUG --from 5-open-pr`
+- `hive finalize SLUG --from 6-review`
+- `hive archive SLUG --from 7-finalize`
+- `hive doctor --json`
+
+When a command returns a non-zero exit, report the exit code and the structured
+JSON envelope when available.
