@@ -0,0 +1,53 @@
+---
+title: Packaging And Install
+type: architecture
+source: tasks/package.rake, packaging/, .github/workflows/release.yml
+created: 2026-07-12
+updated: 2026-07-12
+tags: [packaging, install, release, xdg]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: Hive ships from tagged GitHub Releases as per-platform runtime bundles. Each bundle contains a Ruby prefix, `vendor/bundle`, the Hive app, templates, schemas, and a launcher. Homebrew, AUR `hive-bin`, and `install.sh` all consume the same tarball; the core binary does not install agent skills.
+
+## Runtime Bundle
+
+`rake package` builds `dist/hive-<version>-<triple>.tar.gz` from [[architecture]]:
+
+- `ruby/` — copied Ruby prefix for the target.
+- `vendor/bundle/` — Bundler deployment install, excluding development/test.
+- `app/` — Hive source, templates, schemas, `Gemfile.lock`, docs needed at runtime.
+- `bin/hive` — shell launcher that sets `BUNDLE_GEMFILE`, `BUNDLE_PATH`, `HIVE_BUNDLE_ROOT`, and `HIVE_APP_ROOT`, then execs bundled Ruby with `-rbundler/setup`.
+
+This is deliberate: `bubbletea` and `lipgloss` have platform-specific native gems, so a true single-file Ruby binary is deferred. See `docs/solutions/2026-07-12-runtime-bundle-packaging.md`.
+
+## Install Channels
+
+- Homebrew tap template: `packaging/homebrew/hive.rb.erb`.
+- AUR package template: `packaging/aur/PKGBUILD.erb`.
+- Bash installer: `packaging/install.sh`.
+- Agent prompt installer: `install.md`.
+
+Installers write `install-channel` under `Hive::Config.data_dir`; bundle/package installs also rewrite `INSTALL-CHANNEL` inside the bundle. `hive update` reads those markers and delegates to `brew upgrade ivankuznetsov/hive/hive`, `yay -Syu hive-bin`, or the release installer. Unknown/source installs get a manual `git pull` hint.
+
+## Paths
+
+Fresh installs use XDG:
+
+- config: `~/.config/hive`
+- data: `~/.local/share/hive`
+- state: `~/.local/state/hive`
+- cache: `~/.cache/hive`
+
+Explicit `$HIVE_HOME` wins and preserves the legacy single-directory behavior. If `~/Dev/hive` already exists, it wins over XDG so older source installs continue to read the same `config.yml`. Per-project `.hive-state/` remains project-local by design. See [[modules/config]] and [[state-model]].
+
+## Services
+
+`Hive::Service` renders user-scoped launchd/systemd units from `packaging/launchd/` and `packaging/systemd/`. `hive init` registers the service only during a real interactive run and asks whether to enable/start it now. `hive uninstall` calls the same teardown path.
+
+## Skills
+
+Agent skills live under `packaging/skills/` as a separate marketplace scaffold. The core installer, `hive init`, and `hive uninstall` do not write to `~/.claude`, `~/.codex`, `~/.pi`, or equivalent agent directories.
+
+## Backlinks
+
+- [[architecture]] · [[modules/config]] · [[commands/doctor]] · [[commands/daemon]]
